    "description": "Manappuram Finance is actively seeking a talented and motivated Senior Financial Analyst to join our dynamic team in Vadodara. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout Manappuram Finance:\nManappuram Finance is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Prepare and analyze financial statements, reports, and budgets\n• Monitor market trends and provide investment recommendations\n• Monitor financial performance against targets and provide variance analysis\n• Manage accounts payable and accounts receivable functions\n• Develop financial models and projections for business planning\n• Implement and maintain internal controls and audit procedures\n• Conduct due diligence for mergers, acquisitions, and investments\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• BPharm / MPharm / PharmD\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Tally\n• Proficiency in Financial Modeling\n• Proficiency in IFRS\n• Proficiency in Bloomberg Terminal\n• Proficiency in MS Excel\n• Proficiency in Financial Reporting\n• Proficiency in Budgeting\n• Proficiency in SAP FICO\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Flexible working hours\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Vadodara, Gujarat, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Manappuram Finance!",
